  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Health care and water for 2,000 Togolese enclaved</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Action Committee for Research and Development plans to build a six-room health center to provide first aid to residents living in the remote locality of central Togo, more precisely in the locality of de wissan (prefecture of Blitta), by also providing them with free medicines. This project builds a borehole in the center of wissan, providing communities with potable water and essential hand hygiene training services to 500 children suffering from hand-related diseases,</narrative>
  </description>
